<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN359">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>pāṟupaṭap paṟainta paṉmāṟu maruṅkiṉ</l>
<l>vēṟupaṭu kurala vevvāy kūkaiyoṭu</l>
<l>piṇantiṉ kuṟunari niṇantikaḻ palla</l>
<l>pēey makaḷir piṇantaḻūup paṟṟi</l>
<l>viḷarūṉ ṟiṉṟa vempulāṉ meyyar</l>
<l>kaḷari maruṅkiṉ kālpeyart tāṭi</l>
<l>yīma viḷakkiṉ veruvarap pēruṅ</l>
<l>kāṭumuṉ ṉiṉarē nāṭukoṇ ṭōru</l>
<l>niṉakkum varutal vaika laṟṟē</l>
<l>vacaiyu niṟku micaiyu niṟku</l>
<l>mataṉāl vacainīkki yicaivēṇṭiyu</l>
<l>nacaivēṇṭātu naṉṟumoḻintu</l>
<l>nilavukkōṭṭup palakaḷiṟṟoṭu</l>
<l>polampaṭaiya māmayaṅkiṭa</l>
<l>viḻaikiḷar neṭuntē riravalark karukātu</l>
<l>koḷḷeṉa viṭuvai yāyiṉ veḷḷeṉa</l>
<l>vāṇṭunī peyarnta piṉṉu</l>
<l>mīṇṭunīṭu viḷaṅkunī yeytiya pukaḻē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Even those who have taken land have approached the cremation ground,</l>
<l>where on sides with many changes laid waste when kites descend,</l>
<l>along with hot-mouthed owls of changing(?) voices,</l>
<l>those with fat-glittering teeth, the corpse-eating short jackals,</l>
<l>[and] the Pēy women embrace [and] grip corpses,</l>
<l>[their] bodies reeking of hot flesh as they have eaten white flesh,</l>
<l>dancing, dislodging [their] legs, on the brackish soil</l>
<l>[and] moving frightfully in the lights of the pyres.</l>
<l>For you too will come such a day.</l>
<l>Blame stays and fame stays.</l>
<l>Therefore, repelling blame [and] wanting fame,</l>
<l>not desiring what [you] wish for [and] speaking what is good,</l>
<l>if you let go, saying “take!”, without being scarce, </l>
<l>to mendicants large chariots on which jewels emerge,</l>
<l>while mixing horses with golden gear</l>
<l>with elephant that are many, with moonlight tusks,</l>
<l>clearly, even after you return there</l>
<l>the fame you attained will long shine here.</l>
</lg>
